PLANE-ENGINE param divergences found + fixed, all confirmed closed by a final GUI
kwargs dump (diff_engine_kwargs: create_plane + both repair_planes MATCH; only
benign dry_run/return_results/layer_costs[]-vs-None/routing_layers-None-vs-all6):
  * same_net_pad_clearance (4471cbc) -- create-panel control defaulted to CLEARANCE
    (0.25) vs engine SAME_NET_PAD_CLEARANCE (-1.0). THE BIG ONE: 0.25 blocked plane
    stitches, create left 67 vs 43 unconnected, driving a ~+430-segment plane-repair
    copper overshoot. Fixed by defaulting the "Allow via-in-pad" checkbox ON
    (-> -1.0), in the panel AND reset_params_to_defaults. Post-fix plane-copper delta
    +13 (was +430); GUI board 0 DRC / 4 unconnected (CLI 6).
  * board_edge_clearance (4471cbc + 8b41e5a) -- GUI passed generic BOARD_EDGE_
    CLEARANCE (0.0); planes default PLANE_EDGE_CLEARANCE (0.5). The engine-default
    fix was OVERRIDDEN by the shared Basic-tab routing value merged into the plane
    config, so the FINAL fix is `config.get('board_edge_clearance') or
    PLANE_EDGE_CLEARANCE` (fall back to 0.5 when the shared value is 0/unset, honor
    an explicit positive). Inert on rp2350 (min plane-copper-to-edge 1.285mm, same
    as CLI) but real on edge-hugging boards.
  * min_track_width (4471cbc) -- GUI conflated it with the routing track_width; CLI
    has a separate --min-track-width (REPAIR_MIN_TRACK_WIDTH 0.2). Added a real "Min
    Track Width" control on the repair panel, wired end-to-end: get_config, engine
    call, reset_params_to_defaults, settings_persistence, PARAM_RANGES (already
    present), manifest_to_plan FLAG_PARAMS, claude_plan plan->control mapping.
  * all_layers (8a7f8fa) -- create passed all 6 copper layers; route_planes defaults
    to ['F.Cu']+plane_layers+['B.Cu'] (outer+pour, keeps plane copper off signal
    layers). GUI now mirrors that.
  * no_bga_zone + max_iterations (ef21a30) -- LEAKED from the route tab's shared
    controls into the plane step. Root cause: the plan executor reset params to
    defaults ONCE at load, not before each step, so a route step's
    max_iterations=1000000 / no_bga_zones=ALL persisted into the later plane step.
    Fix: reset_params_to_defaults() before EACH step in _next_step (its docstring
    already claimed this). Interactive single-step runs (clicking a tab button, not
    via the executor) still read live controls, so user edits flow through. Also: on
    normal completion the executor preps the NEXT step's params (loop to step 1 after
    the final) so a pre-plane subset run leaves the plane params visible/editable.

